  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "Circular issued permitting Sri Lanka\u2019s migrant workers to import electric vehicle",
      "author": "",
      "body_lines": [
        "ECONOMYNEXT \u2013 Sri Lanka\u2019s Foreign Employment Minister Manusha Nanayakkara has issued a circular allowing migrant workers to import an electric vehicle in an attempt to incentivise remitting money through formal channels.",
        "Nanayakkara tweeted on Wednesday August 31 that money transmitted from May to December 2022 is eligible for the incentive scheme and will apply to both four-wheeled and two-wheeled vehicles.",
        "Just released d circular letting migrant workers import an electric vehicle \u2013 four wheeler or two wheeler as an incentive to promote remitance through legal and formal channels. Money transmitted from May22 is eligible and will come to an end in December 2022. #ElectricVehicles",
        "On August 01, \u00a0Sri Lanka\u2019s cabinet of ministers approved a proposal by the minister to provide an additional duty concession and electric vehicle import allowance to migrant workers based on the amount they remit to the country through official channels.",
        "Duty, EV allowances to Sri Lanka\u2019s migrant workers who remit via official channels"
      ],
